I need to calculate the Quick Ratio as of the end of the reporting period (2024-02-05).

The Quick Ratio formula is:
Quick Ratio = (Current Assets - Inventory) / Current Liabilities

Let me extract the relevant information from the balance sheet:

Current Assets (end amount): $20,796,970.06
Inventory (end amount): $6,100,000.00
Current Liabilities (end amount): $1,903,121.89

Now I'll calculate:
Quick Ratio = (Current Assets - Inventory) / Current Liabilities
Quick Ratio = ($20,796,970.06 - $6,100,000.00) / $1,903,121.89
Quick Ratio = $14,696,970.06 / $1,903,121.89
Quick Ratio = 7.72

Let me round to 2 decimal places:
Quick Ratio = 7.72
